<subSubSection id="C35F654757282F12F6B1A65A0798FDE8" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BFA36CC57282F15F6B1A65A05B8FF00" blockId="2.[151,1436,1827,2031]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,212]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="46" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="B931EADE57282F14F6B1A65A0571F8B4" bold="true" box="[199,334,1864,1888]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">Etymology.</emphasis>
The genus name, a masculine noun, was formed by appending 
<emphasis id="B931EADE57282F14F24AA65B0048F8B4" box="[1084,1143,1865,1888]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">nigro</emphasis>
- (black), referring to the black coloration of species in the genus, to 
<emphasis id="B931EADE57282F14F40DA67F0680F850" box="[635,703,1901,1924]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">jassus</emphasis>
, a stem commonly used in forming leafhopper genus names. 
<emphasis id="B931EADE57282F14F6B1A682052EF87C" bold="true" box="[199,273,1936,1960]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4F57282F14F76DA683059FF87C" authority="Krishnankutty &amp; Dietrich, 2012" authorityName="Krishnankutty &amp; Dietrich" authorityYear="2012" box="[283,416,1937,1960]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nigrojassus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B931EADE57282F14F76DA683059FF87C" box="[283,416,1937,1960]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">Nigrojassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20257A557282F14F7DCA682062BF873" box="[426,532,1936,1960]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4F57282F14F4C5A6820701F87C" authorityName="Dietrich" authorityYear="1993" box="[691,830,1936,1960]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hoplojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B931EADE57282F14F4C5A6820701F87C" box="[691,830,1936,1960]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">Hoplojassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the following features: body robust; head evenly convex with ocelli situated dorsolaterally on face near eyes; scutellum longer than pronotum; forewing without crossvein r-m 
<number id="3D8D24EB57282F14F7E3A6C505A1F83B" box="[405,414,2007,2031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" value="1.0">1</number>
, appendix broad and extended around wing apex; hindwing R 
<number id="3D8D24EB57282F14F216A6C50051F83B" box="[1120,1134,2007,2031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number id="3D8D24EB57282F14F208A6C500B4F83B" box="[1150,1163,2007,2031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number id="3D8D24EB57282F14F2A9A6C500D7F83B" box="[1247,1256,2007,2031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number id="3D8D24EB57282F14F28FA6C50137F83B" box="[1273,1288,2007,2031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" value="2.0">2</number>
separate and connected by crossvein, hind femur with 
<number id="3D8D24EB57292F15F41BA1850643FF7B" box="[621,636,151,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="3D8D24EB57292F15F4F8A18506A2FF7B" box="[654,669,151,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="3D8D24EB57292F15F4D9A1850686FF7B" box="[687,697,151,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number id="3D8D24EB57292F15F4BDA18506EAFF7B" box="[715,725,151,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" value="1.0">1</number>
macrosetal arrangement; male subgenital plate with numerous scattered macrosetae.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF3A664457292F15F6E1A63005EEF867" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282782/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" targetBox="[166,1428,253,1825]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BFA36CC57292F15F6E1A63005EEF867" blockId="3.[151,1435,1826,1971]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B931EADE57292F15F6E1A6300578F8EC" bold="true" box="[151,327,1826,1849]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">FIGURES 9–22.</emphasis>
Male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4F57292F15F475A6360644F8ED" authorityName="Krishnankutty &amp; Dietrich" authorityYear="2012" box="[515,635,1828,1849]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nigrojassus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B931EADE57292F15F475A6360644F8ED" box="[515,635,1828,1849]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">Nigrojassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. 9–18. 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4F57292F15F56EA63607A7F8ED" authority="Krishnankutty &amp; Dietrich, 2012" authorityName="Krishnankutty &amp; Dietrich" authorityYear="2012" box="[792,920,1827,1849]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nigrojassus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="madhurai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B931EADE57292F15F56EA63607A7F8ED" box="[792,920,1827,1849]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">N. madhurai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20257A557292F15F5E9A63607D1F8ED" box="[927,1006,1828,1849]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
19–22. 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4F57292F15F237A6360092F8ED" authority="Krishnankutty &amp; Dietrich, 2012" authorityName="Krishnankutty &amp; Dietrich" authorityYear="2012" box="[1089,1197,1827,1849]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nigrojassus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ananthi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B931EADE57292F15F237A6360092F8ED" box="[1089,1197,1827,1849]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">N. ananthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20257A557292F15F2C5A636013DF8ED" box="[1203,1282,1828,1849]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
9 &amp; 19. lateral view of genital capsule; 10. dorsal view of pygofer (arrow indicates paired posterodorsal lobes); 11. ventral view of valve; 12. ventral view of subgenital plate; 13. dorsal connective; 14. dorsal view of style and connective; 15. lateral view of style; 16. close-up of connective with middle part of style; 17 &amp; 21. lateral view of aedeagus; 18 &amp; 22. caudal view of aedeagus; 20. caudal view of genital capsule.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BFA36CC572E2F12F6B1A18500CEFF23" blockId="4.[151,1436,151,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
The new genus can be separated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4F572E2F12F4F0A18A072EFF64" authorityName="Dietrich" authorityYear="1993" box="[646,785,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hoplojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B931EADE572E2F12F4F0A18A072EFF64" box="[646,785,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Hoplojassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the following combination of characters: body size much smaller; ocelli near anterior margin of crown; scutellum not surpassing apex of clavus of forewing at rest, not keeled along posterior half; male anal tube without basolateral hook, pygofer with process.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFA36CC572E2F12F6B1A0160798FDE8" blockId="4.[151,1436,151,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4F572E2F12F6B1A016056DFEC8" authorityName="Dietrich" authorityYear="1993" box="[199,338,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hoplojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B931EADE572E2F12F6B1A016056DFEC8" box="[199,338,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Hoplojassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4F572E2F12F7FAA017062EFEC8" authorityName="Krishnankutty &amp; Dietrich" authorityYear="2012" box="[396,529,261,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nigrojassus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B931EADE572E2F12F7FAA017062EFEC8" box="[396,529,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Nigrojassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appear to represent a distinct lineage, separate from other New World 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4F572E2F12F337A01601A4FEC8" box="[1345,1435,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Iassinae">Iassinae</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="B931EADE572E2F12F6D6A03B04E1FE94" box="[160,222,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">sensu</emphasis>
Blocker). As noted by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD44B3D572E2F12F797A03506B1FEEB" author="Dietrich" box="[481,654,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" refString="Dietrich, C. H. (1993) A new genus of Iassinae from Southeastern Brazil (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 95, 475 - 480." type="journal article" year="1993">
Dietrich (
<number id="3D8D24EB572E2F12F43DA03506BAFEEB" box="[587,645,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" value="1993.0">1993</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4F572E2F12F4E2A03A0720FE94" authorityName="Dietrich" authorityYear="1993" box="[660,799,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hoplojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B931EADE572E2F12F4E2A03A0720FE94" box="[660,799,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Hoplojassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
retains a number of features thought to be plesiomorphic for the group as a whole. These include the separate R 
<number id="3D8D24EB572E2F12F481A05E073AFEB0" box="[759,773,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number id="3D8D24EB572E2F12F563A05E071DFEB0" box="[789,802,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number id="3D8D24EB572E2F12F502A05E0742FEB0" box="[884,893,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number id="3D8D24EB572E2F12F5F8A05E07A2FEB0" box="[910,925,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" value="2.0">2</number>
veins in the hind wing; the elongate, sigmoid style; the partially retracted male genital capsule; the large subgenital plates; and the simple connective with a well developed anterior lobe. Such features are shared by the new genus. In contrast, most New World iassines have a number of highly derived morphological features, including fusion of veins R 
<number id="3D8D24EB572E2F12F268A0A50013FE1B" box="[1054,1068,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number id="3D8D24EB572E2F12F24AA0A50076FE1B" box="[1084,1097,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number id="3D8D24EB572E2F12F2D4A0A50094FE1B" box="[1186,1195,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<quantity id="4CBD9B29572E2F12F2CAA0A500D4FE1B" box="[1212,1259,439,463]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
the hind wing, partial or complete loss of the forewing vein separating the inner apical cell from the appendix, and modification of the male genital capsule such that the subgenital plates are reduced and completely concealed by the enlarged pregenital sternite, the connective and styles are also highly modified.
</paragraph>
